@node Hint "Oh, it's an ImageFX ARexx script!!"

Do you have loads of those ugly-dithered pictures? (especially PeeCee losers are very keen in fucking up Hi-Qualtity pictures with the most horrible dithering...)
If you do, you've also tried to restore those pictures to its near-original state. There are several methods to do this, but all of them have their disadvantages:
Some tend to: blur edges, reduce the number of colors or even worse: reduce resolution

@{b}UnDither@{ub} is an ImageFX ARexx script that doesn't have those disadvantages, it only tends to darken some images, but I hope you can live with that.


For those who have studied the script may think 'Is that all?' 
YES it is all there is...
I was just experimenting with different methods of reducing dithering in badly dithered pictures, found a (IMHO) very good method of doing so and made it into an ARexx script...
And I thought well, is there anybody else on this planet that can make use of this shit!?!

@endnode
@node What

Well, any computer capable of running AmigaOS and ImageFX 2.0+ should do...

And it should be nice to have ImageFX 2.6+ too...

But, this script will @{b}NOT@{ub} run on a @{"060" link AHI}!



Well, I guess you'll meet the above requirements and I assume you've got the ImageFX: assign, so @{"press here to install that ............" system "copy UnDither.ifx ImageFX:Rexx"}
@endnode
@Node AHI "Say whot?"

